    "plan_content": "Here's the full plan I've prepared:\n\n---\n\n## Plan: Add `next/geo` Utility Module\n\n### Files (4 new, 1 modified)\n\n| File | Action |\n|------|--------|\n| `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.ts` | Create — core implementation |\n| `packages/next/geo.js` | Create — public CJS entry point |\n| `packages/next/geo.d.ts` | Create — public type definitions |\n| `packages/next/package.json` | Modify — 2 lines in `files` array |\n| `packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts` | Create — 11 unit tests |\n\n### How it follows existing patterns\n\n- **`geo.ts`** → mirrors `user-agent.ts`: no third-party deps, just TypeScript interface + exported functions\n- **`geo.js`** → mirrors `server.js` exactly: namespace object → `module.exports`, then individual `exports.xxx` for named ESM imports; uses `next/dist/` prefix\n- **`geo.d.ts`** → mirrors `server.d.ts` exactly: `export { fn } from 'next/dist/...'`, uses `export type { Geo }` for the interface\n- **`package.json`** → inserts `\"geo.js\"` / `\"geo.d.ts\"` after `form.js`/`form.d.ts` (alphabetical: f < g < r)\n\n### Key technical decisions\n\n- `COUNTRY_NAMES` typed as `Record<string, string | undefined>` — safe index access under all TypeScript strict-mode configurations\n- `headers.get()` returns `null`; `?? undefined` normalizes to `undefined` to match the `Geo` optional fields\n- `x-vercel-ip-country` takes priority over `cf-ipcountry` (via `??` chaining)\n- Haversine formula with Earth radius 6371 km\n- Tests use only `node:test` + `node:assert/strict` (no Jest/external framework)\n\n### Verification\n```bash\npnpm --filter=next types     # TypeScript check\npnpm --filter=next build     # compile to dist/\nnode --test packages/next/src/server/web/spec-extension/geo.test.ts\n```",
